rect.title: Represents any relevant physical thing. Can be either field replaceable or not field replaceable. Note: The model is currently constrained to inside plant.

Indicates whether or not the equipment can be removed and replaced "in the field" (i.e. in a deployment) by normal operations personnel.

Represents a space in an equipment in which another equipment can be fitted in the field.

Represents a connector that may be fully exposed (e.g. to plug in a cable or on the end of a cable) or partially exposed (e.g. backplane to plug in another piece of equipment such as a module). A physical port on the Equipment. A place where signals produced by the functionality of the Equipment may be accessed.

Basic model representing a cable with connectors fitted where the cable is "short" (e.g. patch cord, in-station cabling). This is intentionally a very basic representation of a cable. In a more sophisticated representation cable ends might be represented that then associate to the attached connector. At this point it is assumed that the basic model is sufficient.

Equivalent to the holder for the FRU, represents in the specification a place where one or more types of non-FRU could be present. Unlike the holder what is present is fixed whilst the equipment is in the field.

Rules related to how both non-FRU and FRU presence restricts the potential for additional equipments to be installed. An FRU type installed in one holder may limit the FRU types that can be installed in another holder etc.
